# Margince local environment template
# Copy to .env.local, fill in values, then: source .env.local
# Lines marked [required] cause the server to exit if unset.
# Lines marked [optional] have a working default or gracefully disable a feature.
#
# Scope: this file covers the cmd/server binary, which resolves ALL of its env in
# cmd/server/config.go (the single composition root; enforced by env_guard_test.go).
# The separate cmd/crm-mcp binary reads its own MCP_* vars — see the bottom section.

# ── Database ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# [required] Postgres connection string for the main app database.
# Default matches infra/docker-compose.dev.yml (make infra-up).
DATABASE_URL=postgres://margince:margince@localhost:5432/margince?sslmode=disable

# [optional] Postgres connection string for the integration test database.
# Tests skip cleanly when unset. Create with: make test-db-up
TEST_DATABASE_URL=postgres://margince:margince@localhost:5432/margince_test?sslmode=disable

# ── Redis ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# [optional] Redis URL for the outbox relay + AI result cache.
# When unset the server boots without Redis; the outbox relay and AI caching
# are silently disabled. Default matches the dev compose file.
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0

# ── Server ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# [optional] Listen address for the HTTP server. Default: :8080
# ADDR=:8080

# [optional] Log format. "text" for human-readable dev output; "json" for structured prod logs.
# Default: json
# LOG_FORMAT=text

# [optional] Deployment profile — controls the EGRESS POSTURE for outbound fetches
# (e.g. coldstart web reads / impressum reader). Default: eu_hosted.
# Values: eu_hosted | cloud_frontier | sovereign
# NOTE: this does NOT set the AI-routing profile. The AI router's profile comes
# solely from the `profile:` field inside ai-routing.yaml (see below).
# DEPLOYMENT_PROFILE=eu_hosted

# ── Object storage / blobstore (transcripts + export bundles) ─────────────────
# Backs the transcript-ingest worker (E04) and the workspace export bundle (E11 P10).
# All four are [required together] to ENABLE the feature; if any is missing the
# server still boots but transcript storage + export-to-blob are disabled.
# Defaults match the MinIO service in infra/docker-compose.dev.yml.
# `make run` injects these automatically; set them explicitly for any other launch
# (plain `go run .`, a built binary, a deployed container).
BLOBSTORE_ENDPOINT=localhost:9000
BLOBSTORE_BUCKET=transcripts
BLOBSTORE_ACCESS_KEY=minioadmin
BLOBSTORE_SECRET_KEY=minioadmin
# [optional] Use TLS to reach the blobstore. Default: false (dev MinIO is plain HTTP).
# BLOBSTORE_USE_SSL=false

# ── HubSpot OAuth connector + token vault (B-E18.13) ───────────────────────────
# [required together] to ENABLE the HubSpot connect flow; if any is missing the
# server still boots but /integrations/hubspot/* is not wired (routes.go checks
# HubSpotClientID != "" && KeyVaultEnabled before registering the routes).
# HUBSPOT_CLIENT_ID=
# HUBSPOT_CLIENT_SECRET=
# HUBSPOT_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8080/integrations/hubspot/callback
# KEYVAULT_MASTER_KEY is the base64-encoded 32-byte AES-256 master key for the
# local keyvault.KeyProvider that seals connector_secret ciphertext at rest.
# Generate a dev value with: openssl rand -base64 32
# KEYVAULT_MASTER_KEY=

# ── Approval-gate token seam (X-Approval-Token, gate issue #59) ───────────────
# [required] Root secret for the X-Approval-Token verify/consume seam
# (internal/modules/approvals/token.go). Per-workspace HMAC-SHA256 signing keys
# are derived as HMAC-SHA256(root, workspace_id) — this IS that root. If unset,
# every approval-gated call fails closed (403) with no other startup signal.
# Generate a dev value with: openssl rand -base64 32
# APPROVAL_TOKEN_SIGNING_SECRET=

# ── HubSpot backfill budget (B-E18.16) ───────────────────────────────────────
# [optional] Daily REST limit and conservative cap for the backfill meter.
# Defaults are safe placeholders for local/dev; override for your HubSpot plan.
# OVERLAY_BUDGET_HUBSPOT_REST_LIMIT=40000
# OVERLAY_BUDGET_HUBSPOT_REST_CAP=35000

# ── Speech-to-text / transcription (E04) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. Unset MARGINCE_STT_PROVIDER disables audio transcription; the capture
# pipeline still runs for already-transcribed text.
#   provider: local | cloud
#   profile:  passed through to tier selection (e.g. sovereign forces local-only)
#   endpoint: base URL of the STT/LLM endpoint (e.g. a local Ollama/Whisper server)
#   api_key:  BYOK key for a cloud STT provider (omit for local)
# MARGINCE_STT_PROVIDER=local
# MARGINCE_STT_PROFILE=sovereign
# MARGINCE_STT_ENDPOINT=http://127.0.0.1:11434
# MARGINCE_STT_API_KEY=

# ── AI runtime (EP06) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# [optional] Path to ai-routing.yaml (provider tiers, task routing).
# When unset the AI runtime is disabled; core CRUD and auth work normally.
# Quickstart: cp config/ai-routing.example.yaml config/ai-routing.yaml
AI_ROUTING_CONFIG=config/ai-routing.yaml

# [optional] BYOK API keys for the cloud tiers. These ARE expanded into
# ai-routing.yaml at load time: the file carries `api_key: ${AI_CC_API_KEY}` and
# the value is substituted from this env (os.ExpandEnv) when the router loads.
# An unset key expands to "", which the cloud provider rejects with a clear error.
# Only needed when a tier uses `provider: cloud`. Local/fake tiers need no key.
# AI_CC_API_KEY=
# AI_PF_API_KEY=

# Sovereign / fully-local AI: set profile: sovereign in ai-routing.yaml and define
# a `provider: local` tier pointing at your Ollama endpoint (default
# http://127.0.0.1:11434). No external key required; all inference stays local.

# ── Craftsmanship gate (dev tooling only — not the server) ────────────────────

# [optional] Anthropic API key for the `craft` review gate (cli/craft). The gate
# skips cleanly when unset; it is never read by the server binary.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ── MCP server binary (cmd/crm-mcp — separate process, separate root) ─────────
# These configure the standalone MCP server, NOT cmd/server. They identify the
# Agent Seat Passport the MCP transport runs under. cmd/crm-mcp resolves all of
# its env in cmd/crm-mcp/config.go and fast-fails if a [required] var is unset.
# DATABASE_URL (above) is also [required] by this binary; REDIS_URL is optional
# (defaults to localhost), same as cmd/server.
# MCP_PASSPORT_ID=                          # [required] agent-seat passport id
# MCP_WORKSPACE_ID=                         # [required] tenant the seat operates in
# MCP_GRANTED_BY=                           # [optional] who granted the seat
# MCP_AGENT_SCOPES=person:read,deal:read    # [optional] comma-separated
# MCP_HUMAN_SCOPES=person:read,deal:read    # [optional] comma-separated

# ── Hosted HTTPS MCP server binary (cmd/crm-mcp-http) ─────────────────────────
# Shares all of the MCP_* vars above (this binary resolves them the same way,
# in cmd/crm-mcp-http/config.go), plus these HTTP/TLS-only vars:
# MCP_HTTP_ADDR=                            # [optional] listen address, defaults to :8443
# MCP_HTTP_TLS_CERT=                        # [optional] TLS cert path — set together with MCP_HTTP_TLS_KEY to terminate TLS in-binary
# MCP_HTTP_TLS_KEY=                         # [optional] TLS key path
# MCP_OAUTH_WORKSPACE_ID=                   # [optional] enables OAuth2/PKCE/DCR when set; workspace that owns registered OAuth clients
# MCP_PASSPORT_TTL=                         # [optional] access-token lifetime for OAuth-minted passports (e.g. 1h, 30m); defaults to 1h
